metadata.name: Memories of Kowloon Walled City
metadata.description:
Kowloon Walled City was the densest place on earth. It was a hastily put together conglomerate of tiny apartments, one on top of the other, caged balconies slapped onto the sides and connected through a labyrinth of damp, dark corridors. 

This informal city was not only a hotbed for organized crime, but also a vibrant community of commerce and hope.

Not to say that this wasn’t home to a lot of people and that no “fond memories” were formed there, but still, like all slums, it was a tough place to live, fraught with contradictions in the haze of hope for a better life.
